---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import QuantumHardwareComparisonChartApex from "../components/qdaria-business-plan/charts/QuantumHardwareComparisonChartApex.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="Quantum Hardware Comparison Chart Test">
  <div class="container mx-auto py-8 px-4">
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-8 text-center">Quantum Hardware Comparison Chart</h1>
    
    <div class="bg-slate-800 rounded-lg p-6 max-w-4xl mx-auto">
      <QuantumHardwareComparisonChartApex
        id="quantum-hardware-test"
        showDataTable={true}
        showControls={true}
      />
    </div>

    <div class="mt-12 max-w-4xl mx-auto">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Implementation Details</h2>
      <p class="mb-4">
        This chart demonstrates the ApexCharts implementation with SVG fallback for the Quantum Hardware Comparison
        visualization. Key features include:
      </p>
      
      <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-6 space-y-2">
        <li>Reliable SVG fallback implementation</li>
        <li>Web worker-based data processing</li>
        <li>ARIA accessibility attributes</li>
        <li>Keyboard navigation</li>
        <li>Selectable text elements</li>
        <li>Responsive design</li>
        <li>Data table toggle functionality</li>
        <li>$1 Trillion market milestone annotation</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 mt-8">Chart Design</h2>
      <p>
        The chart visualizes quantum hardware performance metrics across major quantum computing
        companies. QDaria's hardware-agnostic approach is highlighted, showcasing how QDaria provides
        access to the best capabilities of each platform rather than being limited to a single hardware
        architecture.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
